quoted_tweet.text:
A benchmark showing that ts-pattern is surprisingly faster than you'd think.

It takes ~0.88 ms for it to match 1k random objects. 

pattycake removes the runtime overhead so it runs in 0.01ms, but for most usecases that perf boost is negligible

"JIT happens" https://t.co/HQYv2anraf

text:
This is cool.
TS-Pattern is faster than most people think, and it's unlikely for code branching to be the perf bottleneck of your app, but compiling its runtime away is an interesting idea for perf critical code. Thank you for exploring this path @aidenybai & @zack_overflow!
